{"word":"παλάσσω","slug":"παλάσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παλάσσω</b></el> <el>(πᾰλάσσω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πάλλω'><el>πάλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to besprinkle, sully, defile</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; mostly in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>παλάσσετο χεῖρας</el> <i>he defiled his</i> hands, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> also of things, <i>to be scattered abroad</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> of <i>lots shaken</i> in an urn, <el>κλήρῳ πεπαλάχθαι</el> <i>to determine</i> one's <i>fate</i> by lot, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>πάλος.</el><p/></div>"}]}